flowRoot.flowPara: I suspect the real reason that was decided is because it would be too easy for authors to screw up. background: green, url(image.jpg); would "fail" in a sense in that it would just flood the background green. Forcing the color to be last makes the color kind of like a "fallback" rather than a layer like any other.

Unfortunately we also can't simply leave the color at the bottom and adjust the opacity of the image to allow some of that color to come through, because background-opacity isn't a thing. (Although you can kind of fake it.)
